results.name: Keeping Your Vision Out in Front
results.description:
When your memories exceed your dreams, the end is near.
We can't be satisfied with the status quo, even when it's wonderful.

results.name: Leading in Uncertain Times
results.description: During times of uncertainty, leaders need to lean heavily into two things: clarity and flexibility.

results.name: Stumbling Along
results.description:
1-PART message from Andy Stanley: Growth, accountability, belonging and 
care happen in community groups - in circles, not rows. It's easy to 
stumble away from faith when you are a nameless person sitting in a row 
on Sunday morning. But it's almost impossible to stumble away - or to 
stay away - when you're in community, doing life with a group of people.
 In this message, Andy reminds us that Jesus said stumbling blocks are 
inevitable. But pity those who fall and have no one to help them up.

results.name: Life Apps
results.description: 6-PART series from Andy Stanley & Jeff Henderson: Be a DOER, not just a HEARER. Application makes all the difference.

results.name: Why in the World
results.description:
Why would God leave the comfort and recognition of heaven to live on this ball of dirt in a time before morphine and indoor plumbing when the best of conditions barely paralleled the worst of modern day conditions? Why?

We think we know why He died. But what compelled him to live as one of us?


NOTE: This series planning kit provides a communicator with the assets they need to re-preach the messages themselves. Series planning kits include many of the assets from a message series, but without screen feeds.

NOTE: This series has it’s own website: whyseries.org.

results.name: Wish You Were Here
results.description:
5-PART series from Clay Scroggins, Andy Stanley, Jeff Henderson and Benjamin Watson: Whether it's your health, your relationships, your finances, or your 
faith, there's an area of your life in which you can't seem to make 
progress. But what if there was a way to get from where you are to where
 you want to be?

attachments.filename: Wish You Were Here Pt1 NP Clay.mp3
Wish You Were Here Pt2 NP - Clay.mp3

results.name: Bottom of the Ninth
results.description: 4-PART series from Jeff Henderson, Clay Scroggins and Gavin Adams: When you feel down and out, you may be down, but you’re never out. There is still hope. Sure, you may be behind. It may be the Bottom of the 9th, but there is still a chance to turn this game around.

results.name: See the World
results.description:
5-PART series from Clay Scroggins, Andy Stanley and Evan McLaughlin: Family, friends, education, personal experience—plenty of things influence how you see the world. But how does the way you see the world affect you? What if you’re missing a bigger picture?


NOTE: This series planning kit provides a communicator with the assets they need to re-preach the messages themselves. Series planning kits include many of the assets from a message series, but without screen feeds.

results.name: How to Get What You Really Want
results.description:
What do you want in 2017? Is it a what? Is it a who? Maybe it's a state 
of mind. Are you sure it's what you really want? Let's figure it out 
together.

results.name: Me & My Big Mouth
results.description: Open mouth . . . insert foot. Don’t we all wish we could avoid that scenario? Our words can get us into all kinds of trouble. But maybe we can learn to keep our big mouths in check.

results.name: Relationship Rules
results.description:
3-PART series from Clay Scroggins: After this year, it might feel as though there is a lot at stake in our world, our country, and our city. But consider the relationships in your life that might be at stake as well. After all, the quality of our lives is only as good as the quality of our relationships. For a fresh take on some forgotten rules in our relationships, join Clay for, Relationship Rules.

Fonts include Palmer LakePrint and Titling Gothic.

results.name: For ATL
results.description:
2-PART online series from Clay Scroggins: For too long the church in America has been known for what it is against. At Buckhead Church, we want to be known for who we are for.

Note: This localized series is available for inspiration. Due to specific campus branding, editable key art is not available.

results.name: Better for All
results.description:
1-PART message from Tensley Almand:
After one year of meeting in our first non-portable location, there's so much we love about our church. Looking back, it's been an incredible year. Looking forward, there's one thing we hope never changes.

Note: There is neither editable key art nor a title package included with this message.

results.name: Everyone is Included
results.description:
1-PART message from Tensley Almand: Has it ever felt like church is only for church people? Like Sundays are great for people who are already in the club, but for the rest of us there’s just something missing? But when we look at the way the church launched in the first century, nothing could be further from the truth.

Note: No fonts, key art assets or discussion questions included with this local message.

results.name: Winning
results.description: 1-PART message from Andy Stanley: We all want to win. After all, winning is better than not winning. In a game a win is defined, but life is not a game. And winning in the most important areas of our lives isn’t always clear. So, how do we win?

results.name: You've Got Style
results.description:
4-Part Series from Sean Seay and Gerald Fadayomi: Fashion, home decor, even online—there are many different ways of expressing ourselves. We call it style and we all have one. Even the way we draw near to God has a style. Quiet, loud, inside, outdoors, intellectual, enthusiastic and more. Explore the various styles of connecting with God and discover more of how you’re wired. The answers may surprise you!

Font: Brandon Grotesque, Underland Alternative
Note: This series includes IMAG video feeds only.

results.name: This is How We Change the World
results.description:
3-PART series from Reed Moore, Brooklynn Warren and Gerald Fadayomi: We 
all want to make a difference. We want our actions to matter. Some 
actions have a profound effect on us and those around us. These are 
actions we should double down on. These actions are how we can change 
the world.

In this 3-session study, your group will explore the upside-down and inside-out life that God invites us into.


The videos and discussion guides for this 3-part study are available for free on groupleaders.org.

results.name: MS: Sticks and Stones
results.description:
3-PART series: It is splashed all over the news and displayed on posters throughout the schools. Bullying has been depicted on TV screens and written about in books, but few students have engaged in real conversations about the topic. Our goal is to make Transit the safest place to talk about anything, including bullying. It can take many forms at this age, and the high value on friendships heightens the impact of bullies during middle school. So, let’s spend the next three weeks being open and honest about feeling intimidated in our series Sticks and Stones.


Note: New parent mailer included.

results.name: HS Stuff Christians Do
results.description:
3-PARTS: In this series, we’re taking a closer look at some of the things Christians do that might seem a little weird from the outside until you understand them. But once you do, you realize they’re actually life -giving. They’re not about checking boxes or earning points with God. They’re about transformation that shapes us and connects us to Jesus!

Talk 1: Baptism is our public display of a personal decision to follow Jesus.
Talk 2: Communion is about what Jesus did and what he’s going to do.
Talk 3: Prayer is relational, not transactional.


Note: It may be helpful to do a leader huddle up/ leader meeting before your baptism and communion weeks to help cast vision.

results.name: Devotional: Before Bethlehem
results.description:
10-PART Reading Plan: A 10-Day Journey Through 10 Stories Leading to the Birth of a Savior


You likely know the story of Jesus’s birth—the star, the manger, the shepherds—but the story didn’t start there. Long before that night in Bethlehem, God was already at work—through ordinary people, unexpected moments, and promises that pointed toward a coming Rescuer.


In Before Bethlehem, we’ll trace 10 key moments in Scripture that paved the way for the birth of Jesus. These stories and prophecies reveal God’s faithfulness, his plan of redemption, and his love that has been unfolding since the beginning.

Join us December 15 to December 24 for this 10-day devotional as we unpack the wonder of how God was writing the story of Christmas years before the manger.


Note: This content is designed to engage digitally unknown individuals and endear them to your church. 
Participants register at https://northpoint.org/christmas-devotional
They are then texted daily audio devotionals.


The goal is to have participants register, so that you can follow up with next steps, i.e. invitation to Christmas services.
